      "content": "Those distinct clusters might indeed signal a different underlying process, which is a classic problem when dealing with complex data. You could try segmenting your data first—perhaps by grouping the characteristics of those clustered points—and then running separate models for each segment. If the clusters are truly different, a single model won't capture both the general trend and the special behavior of those specific groups. This approach, sometimes called mixture modeling, helps you treat different populations with different rules.",
